comments: Brown (BOS) lets the ball bounce in-between dribbles and legally resumes his dribble.
Smart (BOS) is firming up in Tucker's (PHI) path and he absorbs the contact.
Reed (PHI) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Brogdon (BOS) does not step out of bounds when he receives the pass.
Reed (PHI) and Smart (BOS) come together at the same spot as they pursue the rebound, and the contact is marginal.
Harden (PHI) steps forward into Tatum's (BOS) path and makes foot to foot contact with Tatum that affects his shot near the rim.
Horford (BOS) brushes Harden's (PHI) arm after his gather and the contact prior to the pass is marginal.

A shooting foul is called on Smart (BOS), and after communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court was confirmed.  Smart does not establish a legal guarding position in Maxey's (PHI) path prior to contact.
Smart (BOS) and Tucker (PHI) come together at the same spot, and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the rebound.
Reed (PHI) contests Brogdon's (BOS) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Tucker (PHI) applies his forearm to Horford's (BOS) side and the contact during the shot near the rim is marginal.
Tucker (PHI) applies his hands to Tatum's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs as Tucker immediately removes his hands from Tatum.
Reed (PHI) is already in Smart's (BOS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Smart (BOS) lowers his arm and initiates arm contact with Reed (PHI) that affects his shot near the rim.
Tucker (PHI) and Tatum (BOS) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Harris (PHI) brings his hands towards Brown's (BOS) front and marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
Tatum (BOS) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Maxey (PHI) gains possession of the ball just as the shot clock horn sounds, and play correctly continues.
Harris (PHI) places his hand momentarily on Tatum's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Harris (PHI) swipes his arm down and makes arm contact with Tatum (BOS) that affects his driving shot attempt.
Tucker (PHI) firms up in Smart's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact as Smart goes under the pick.
Horford (BOS) legally contests Harden's (PHI) jump shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) and Harden (PHI) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Harden (PHI) places his hand to Smart's (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Tatum (BOS) swipes his hand down and makes contact with Reed's (PHI) arm that affects his ability to pass.
